items.title: Homicide investigation underway after fatal stabbing in WA carpark
items.standfirst: A homicide investigation is underway after a man was stabbed to death in a shopping centre carpark in Perth's south.
items.content: A homicide investigation is underway after a man was fatally stabbed in a shopping centre carpark in Perth's south. Detectives spent the day combing through the scene today, trying to piece together what happened with a pool of blood a sign of what's unfolded. Police were called to Talisker Gate in Aubin Grove around 10.40pm last night, where they found a man with stab wounds. READ MORE: Riot squad arrives at pop-up party at Sydney beach He was taken to hospital but he couldn't be saved. Some residents told 9News they saw a vehicle enter and leave the carpark around the time but didn't hear anything alarming. Many unaware of the crime scene on their doorstep until this morning.READ MORE: White Christmas for parts of Tasmania as sun shines on Bondi Exactly what happened and what the man was stabbed with is still under investigation. Police are asking anyone with information to come forward. clusters.title: Crane hits Gold Coast building after snapping in storm
clusters.neutral_headline: Crane hits Gold Coast building after snapping in storm

items.title: Crane hits Gold Coast building after snapping in storm
items.standfirst: A crane has hit a building after a powerful Christmas Day storm hit the south-east Queensland region, leading to evacuations.
items.content: A powerful storm smashed parts of the Gold Coast, causing Christmas Day destruction at a holiday park and snapping a crane.The quick but intense storm cut power to 6000 homes across Brisbane, Gold Coast and the Somerset regions, with Energex crews currently trying to restore power.Southport was one of the worst impacted areas, with trees and power lines down across the suburb as the clean up begins.READ MORE: 'This Christmas is a different one', says Albanese as he serves festive meals The Christmas storm - known as a microburst - was so strong, it almost blew open restaurant doors and managed to send a barbeque flying.It also snapped a large crane, which hit a Gold Coast apartment building and halted Christmas festivities for the afternoon.At the Broadwater Tourist Park next door, holidaymakers were asked to evacuate as debris was strewn across the site.Tents were twisted and torn apart, even a boat was flipped by the storm."We've got family in the park and we went down to help out because our parents, their gazebo had smashed into a caravan," holidaymaker Taylor Grigore told 9News."Caravans were moving in the wind, people were trying to run out to grab their stuff and it was just crazy."As quickly as it came, the storm was over.Emergency services were on standby but no-one was injured."No one is going to forget this Christmas I don't reckon here," holidaymaker Mitchell Hall said.DOWNLOAD THE 9NEWS APP: Stay across all the latest in breaking news, sport, politics and the weather via our news app and get notifications sent straight to your smartphone. Available on the Apple App Store and Google Play.
